{"word":"ἐρεμνός","slug":"ἐρεμνός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐρεμνός</b></el> <el>(ἐρεμνός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:syncopated'>syncop.</a> from <a href='S:ἐρεβεννός'><el>ἐρεβεννός</el></a> \n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <el>Ἔρεβος</el>\n<p/><i>black, swart, dark</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>ἐρεμνὴ φάτις</el> a <i>dark, obscure</i> rumour, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/>"}]}